  • Method Details

    • LoginButton

      public void LoginButton()
      Is used to determine what the text of the login button will show. If not logged on, it will allow the user to log on. If the user is logged on, it will allow them to logoff. If the user is an Admin it will display a slightly different message when logging off.

    • submissionCheck

      public void submissionCheck()
      Scans part of Catalog.txt to display catalogged applications. Removes all elements from the panel before adding all catalogged applications back, allowing this to be called to refresh visible applications.

    • alphabeticalSort

      public void alphabeticalSort​(java.lang.String[] str)
      This is used to sort our buttons alphabetically by sorting an array of our app's titles and then scanning through "Catalog.txt" to re-add the buttons.
      Parameters:
